|
| A. sudanensis               | None                                              | Feeds on grass species (Poaceae). Feeding on leaves results in yellow streaks as leaves matures. Widespread in Australia. |
| Chaetanaphothri ps leeuweni | Bananarust thrips                                 | Feeds and breeds on leaves of Musa spp. Only known from NT. |
| C. orchidii                 | Orchid thrips, banana thrips                      | Feeds and breeds on leaves of orchids, Musa spp., Citrus and some greenhouse plants. Present in SA, NSW and Qld. On banana it can cause markings on fruit and leaves. |
| C. signipennis              | Banana thrips, orchid thrips                      | Main hosts are anthurium, dracaena and banana, but may also feed on citrus, tomato, orchids and beans. Present in Qld, NT and NSW                                                                                                 |
| Dichromothrips corbetti     | Orchid thrips                                     | Venda spp. found in NT and Qld. Feeds and breeds on leaves and flowers. |
| Echinothrips americanus     | Poinsettia thrips                                 | Impatiens, Euphorbia pulcherrima , Dieffenbachia, Syngonium, Cardamine and Hibiscus. Feeds and breeds on leaves. |
| Frankliniella occidentalis  | Western flower thrips (WFT)                       | Fruit, vegetable, flower and ornamental crops. It has been recorded on over 250 plant species.